# Email Configuration
# Choose your email service provider

# Option 1: Gmail/Google Workspace (recommended)
EMAIL_SERVICE=gmail
EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=your-email@gmail.com

# Option 2: Custom SMTP (alternative)
# EMAIL_SERVICE=smtp
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.your-provider.com  
# SMTP_PORT=587
# EMAIL_USER=your-email@your-domain.com
# EMAIL_PASS=your-email-password
# EMAIL_FROM=your-email@your-domain.com

# For Gmail Setup:
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication in your Google Account
# 2. Generate an App Password: https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/185833
# 3. Use the 16-character app password (not your regular password)
# 4. Set EMAIL_USER to your full Gmail address
# 5. Set EMAIL_PASS to the app password (no spaces)

# For other email providers:
# Contact your hosting provider for SMTP settings
# Common settings:
# - Port 587 (STARTTLS) or 465 (SSL)  
# - Authentication required
# - Use your hosting email credentials